S. African Equities: Anglo American, BHP Billiton, Exxaro, SacOil, Sasol

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-05-23T16:10:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/south-african-stocks-decline-anglo-american-falls-to-lowest-since-dec-2.html
The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index
fell to the lowest closing level since March 23, dropping
449.60, or 1.4 percent, to 31,344.53 at the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  Anglo American Plc (AGL)  , the diversified mining company
that makes up 10 percent of  South Africa ’s benchmark stock
index, dropped to the lowest closing level since Dec. 2,
slipping 6.55 rand, or 2 percent, to 322.45 rand. Copper slumped
as much as 3.7 percent to $8,732 a metric ton on the London
Metal Exchange.  China ’s manufacturing growth eased for a second
consecutive month in May, according to a preliminary survey by
HSBC Holdings Plc and Markit Economics.  BHP Billiton Plc (BIL)  , the world’s largest mining
company, declined to the lowest close since March 28, dropping
2.27 rand, or 0.9 percent, to 261.15 rand.  Exxaro Resources Ltd. (EXX)  , a coal-mining company,
declined for a seventh day, retreating 8.50 rand, or 5.2
percent, to 154.50 rand. The coal producer will pay A$123
million ($130 million) for  Australia ’s Territory Resources Ltd.
to gain iron-ore assets, it said in a statement today.  SacOil Holdings Ltd. (SCL SJ), an oil and natural gas
explorer, reached the lowest closing level since Oct. 13,
falling 27 cents, or 21 percent, to 1 rand. SacOil dropped a
plan to sell stock to selected investors and started a probe
into movements in its securities amid concern about possible
share-price manipulation, it said in a regulatory filing today.  Sasol Ltd. (SOL)  , the world’s biggest maker of motor
fuel from coal, fell 8.16 rand, or 2.3 percent, to 346.84 rand.
Oil declined as much as 3.1 percent to $96.37 a barrel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
